SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 68, Chapter 211, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) There is created the advisory task force on solid waste to examine and
review issues related to solid waste. The task force shall focus its examination and
review on innovative processes for the disposition of solid waste and shall review all
aspects of the disposition of solid waste that the task force determines to be necessary,
including, but not limited to, landfilling, recycling, incineration, agricultural uses, and
energy production.
(b) The task force must be composed of fifteen (15) members, as follows:
(1) The governor, or the governor's designee;
(2) The chair of the energy, agriculture and natural resources committee
of the senate, or the chair's replacement. If the chair of the energy, agriculture
and natural resources committee of the senate is unable to serve for any reason,
then the speaker of the senate may designate an alternate senate member to
serve as a replacement for the chair from the chair's respective committee;
(3) The chair of the committee of the house of representatives with
jurisdiction over subject matters pertaining to solid waste disposal, or the chair's
replacement. If the chair of the committee of the house of representatives with
jurisdiction over subject matter areas pertaining to solid waste disposal is unable
to serve for any reason, the speaker of the house of representatives may
